Coal From Richards Bay, South Africa, Rose 0.3% to $119.89 a Ton Last Week

-- B y   A l i s t a i r   H o l l o w a y
-- 
2011-03-14T09:29:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/coal-from-richards-bay-south-africa-rose-0-3-to-119-89-a-ton-last-week.html
Prices for coal shipped from  South
Africa ’s  Richards Bay , the continent’s biggest export facility
for the fuel, rose 0.3 percent to $119.89 a metric ton last
week, according to IHS McCloskey. The data are an average based
on daily price assessments and a market survey. Australian
coking coal rose 0.7 percent to $327.85 a ton.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alistair Holloway in London at 
